text:
I try the Laksa from HOCKLAN.

It served with the standard ingredients and the taste is nice. Price is so affordable. Will come back again if pass by here the next time ü§≠üí™üèºüëç

This is a neighborhood non-airconditioned food court and is made up of 2 separate locations. It has some popular stalls where there are always a queue for the food (e.g. Prawn Noodle stall and Wanton Noodle stall).

Food wise is ok at this coffeshop. Êª°Â†ÇÁ∫¢ mala xiang guo is good. Reasonable price & portion. U can request for less spicy.
Sub standard tea/kopi. No tea taste. They just keep making tea with same pot of tea leaf, didn't bother to change.
Tea/kopi at another coffeeshop nearby, Foodloft is much much better. They will standby few brews of tea/ kopi so the kopi/ tea taste so much better & worth $ spent. Both coffeeshops charge same prices for kopi/ tea.
The tzer char here is tasty and underrated.  My bro loves their salted fish chicken so much

Beside another coffee shop sell wanton Mee and western food. This Thais food is worth to mention. First time try. The rice is soft and nice, kangkong veg is nice and cheap at 5 dollar n the portion is a lot. Worth to try and support.
